</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[189,1399,1562,1695]" pageId="23" pageNumber="70">
<taxonomicName authority="Grichanov, 2021" authorityName="Grichanov" authorityYear="2021" box="[189,525,1562,1588]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Amblypsilopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andasibensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,525,1562,1588]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="70">Amblypsilopus andasibensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[536,630,1563,1589]" pageId="23" pageNumber="70" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is very close to 
<taxonomicName authority="Grichanov, 2021" authorityName="Grichanov" authorityYear="2021" box="[840,941,1562,1589]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Amblypsilopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="olgae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[840,941,1562,1589]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="70">A. olgae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[952,1047,1563,1589]" pageId="23" pageNumber="70" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in habitus. The latter differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Grichanov, 2021" authorityName="Grichanov" authorityYear="2021" box="[255,441,1598,1624]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Amblypsilopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andasibensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[255,441,1598,1624]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="70">A. andasibensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[449,541,1598,1624]" pageId="23" pageNumber="70" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in the fore tarsomeres 4–5 white. The fore tarsomere 4 is entirely black in 
<taxonomicName authority="Grichanov, 2021" authorityName="Grichanov" authorityYear="2021" box="[219,405,1633,1660]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Amblypsilopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="70" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="andasibensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[219,405,1633,1660]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="70">A. andasibensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[413,507,1634,1660]" pageId="23" pageNumber="70" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
; the long lobe of the cercus has 2 long setae at the middle, but no modified setae at the apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="23" pageNumber="70" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="23.[189,324,1735,1761]" box="[189,324,1735,1761]" pageId="23" pageNumber="70">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,324,1735,1761]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="23" pageNumber="70" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,1735,1761]" pageId="23" pageNumber="70">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="23.[188,1398,1781,1914]" pageId="23" pageNumber="70">
The species is named after the Andasibe-Mantadia National Park located about 
<quantity box="[1203,1298,1781,1808]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="23" pageNumber="70" unit="km" value="150.0">150 km</quantity>
east of 
<collectingRegion box="[189,352,1817,1843]" country="Madagascar" name="Antananarivo" pageId="23" pageNumber="70">Antananarivo</collectingRegion>
, consisting principally of primary growth forest of the Alaotra-Mangoro Region in eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[188,332,1852,1878]" name="Madagascar" pageId="23" pageNumber="70">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
. The park’s two component parts are Mantadia National Park and Analamazoatra Reserve (
<bibRefCitation author="Newsome D. &amp; Hassell S." box="[197,511,1888,1914]" pageId="23" pageNumber="70" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref20968" refString="Newsome D. &amp; Hassell S. 2014. Tourism and conservation in Madagascar: the importance of Andasibe National Park. Koedoe 56 (2): a 1144 (1 - 8 pp.). https: // doi. org / 10.4102 / koedoe. v 56 i 2.1144" type="book chapter" year="2014">Newsome &amp; Hassell 2014</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
